source: Linda M Wooten for U.S. Senate
text: I urge all Republicans who will be attending the Maine Republican Convention to vote for @Amy Colter to be the Republican nominee for U.S. Senate, rather than Susan Collins. I will still be on the ballot as an Independent in November but, since Amy and I share the same stance on the issues, I think if either of us gets elected, we'll be in fine shape to help this country move forward!

source: Linda M Wooten for U.S. Senate
text: For anyone who would like me to visit their town for a Meet & Greet, I ask that you set it up by first checking with your town and getting approval to meet at a particular place. It can be your own home, the townhall, a restaurant or coffee shop, etc. Get some dates and times that the venue will allow you to meet. Email me with the times and dates available so that I can make sure I'm not already booked!  LMWooten@outlook.com After we coordinate a date and time, you will need to schedule it with the venue. Invite people to attend! The day before the meeting, follow-up with those you've invited to make sure they will attend! I am available most weekends or during the week in the evening if it's close to Androscoggin County or Cumberland County.  I look forward to meeting as many of you as possible! Thank you for your interest and support! WWW.WootenForMe.com

source: Linda M Wooten for U.S. Senate
text: OK, folks, we need your help collecting signatures to put Linda's name on the November ballot.  Have you signed the petition yet? If not, we need you to do so as soon as possible.  Various people have them all over the state, but you do have to be registered to vote in Maine.  If you need help finding someone with a petition in your area, please just send us a note so we know what area you live in. Thank you for supporting Linda's campaign to become the next U.S. Senator for Maine.

source: Linda M Wooten for U.S. Senate
Linda M Wooten for U.S. Senate
text: I support "Yes" on 1.  "Linda Wooten of Auburn, an independent candidate for the U.S. Senate, said she supports repeal of the law in order to preserve parental choice “to take care of their children the best way they feel fit.” She said that many parents who pushed for the referendum have allowed their children to receive immunizations. “That is not the issue,” Wooten said. “The issue with the mandate is that it takes away the parent’s right to take care of their children in the way that is best” for their own children. “Parents feel this is a dangerous precedent that will grow into more mandates if not stopped,” Wooten said.   Follow me: www.wootenforme.com  #wootenmaine  or https://www.facebook.com/Linda-M-Wooten-for-US-Senate-100592344818530/ https://www.sunjournal.com/2020/02/28/republicans-democrats-split-on-whether-to-back-question-1/?utm_source=Headlines&utm_medium=email&utm_campaign=Daily
